7/ And thus began the long week. Fever came and went. Kept taking my antibiotic. Slowly but surely I began to feel better. It took me to about Sunday, nearly a full week after the first signs, to feel somewhat normal again.

@IndyIllini Doxycycline. Yes, they took the test for COVID-19 while at the hospital on a Tuesday and get the results that next Monday.

5/ We called the corona virus hotline and they told us to go to the ER. So we did. I was brought back and they began some tests. Flu - negative. Chest X-ray. Clear at first glance. They told me they’d submit a COVID-19 test.

1/ Thank you all so much for your thoughts and prayers. It wasn’t fun letting everyone know I tested positive for COVID-19 but felt it was necessary.  I feel REALLY GOOD now and am over the worst of it, but here’s my story.

As someone who just found out today they tested positive for COVID-19 this is very shortsighted by our government. I have ZERO idea where I might have gotten it. Social distancing is the smartest, but not easiest, option. Hope they wise up. https://t.co/5sSAf8Z2wQ

4/ I’m always warm. Not feverish warm, but sweaty warm. Fans on me in my room, etc.... Tuesday I couldn’t get warm. So I jumped in the shower. I got warm. But then I couldn’t get a good breath. My cuticles turned blue according to me wife.
